cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses physical layer security in wireless communication, which involves information theory and communication networks. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses signal processing enhancements, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions large-scale decentralized wireless networks, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
